are you happy with just one child are you the type of parent who was put off having any more children or always planned just one child or can you not bear to leave it at one i have one baby we tried desperately to get her and i have to say i didn't know it was going to be so hard the whole feeding problems sleeping problems teething hands in everything everything in mouth temper tantrums restrictions everything has to be routine not saying im unhappy i love her to bits and wouldn't change a thing but i have to say its put me off having another i can't imagine how mothers cope with more than kids i was one of children the oldest and it was a nightmare the oldest goes without the youngest is spoilt parents don't have enough time to spend quality time with each one individually and then theres the financial side we can cope with baby but theres always things to buy so yes im happy with just one my husband wants more but i've told him as soon as men are able to become preggers i'll happily comply Humphrey Bogart Knots Landing Shaggy dog story About a Boy Pitaten EastEnders The Beatles discography Baby Blues Breastfeeding The Fairly OddParents Kodocha Friends Boston Public W.I.T.C.H. Autism John the Baptist Marilyn Monroe Adoption Eric Cartman Episodes of Lost (Season 1) 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Laura Schlessinger Married... with Children Romeo and Juliet Sleeping Murder Marie Antoinette Theory of conduct Futurama (TV series - season 5) Divorce The Amber Spyglass Sunset Beach (soap opera) Infantilism The Smoking Room Characters in the Smurfs Ayyavazhi mythology Childbirth Cat The Giver Princess Marie-Th__r__se-Charlotte Grief The Secret Garden The Human Stain Ocean's Twelve Doug Drill bit Care Bears Avenue Q The Lovely Bones The Catcher in the Rye Miss Saigon The Family from One End Street Property (ownership right) Eric Bischoff History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder The Young Ones (TV series) Jon Secada Asperger syndr